# code-review-graph (Pump)

This repo has a local Tree-sitter knowledge graph via the **code-review-graph** MCP server.

**Prefer graph tools before Grep/Glob/Read** when exploring structure, callers, impact, or reviewing diffs. Fall back to file tools only when the graph lacks coverage (e.g. new unindexed files, generated assets, or Solana IDL JSON).

## When to use first

| Task | Tool |
|---|---|
| Find symbol / how X works | `semantic_search_nodes` or `query_graph` |
| Blast radius / dependents | `get_impact_radius` |
| Review local or PR diffs | `detect_changes` + `get_review_context` |
| Callers / callees / imports / tests | `query_graph` (`callers_of`, `callees_of`, `imports_of`, `tests_for`) |
| Architecture map | `get_architecture_overview` + `list_communities` |

Start reviews with `get_minimal_context` when available; use `detail_level="minimal"` and escalate only if needed.

## Pump scope hints

- Web UI: `apps/web/src/`
- Solana indexer: `apps/indexer-sol/`
- Program: `programs/pump-launchpad/`
- Admin: `apps/admin/`
- Do not treat ClickHouse / Redis / deploy scripts as a substitute for position/cost-basis truth — graph helps navigate code, not runtime data.

## Keep graph fresh

After large refactors or pulling main: `code-review-graph update` (or `build` if DB missing). Optional: `code-review-graph watch` during long sessions.
